First, we need to exponentiation each of the coefficients.

10

00:00:29,995  -->  00:00:33,325
Then, with quantitative variables we would say,

11

00:00:33,325  -->  00:00:36,295
for a one unit increase in your explanatory variable,

12

00:00:36,295  -->  00:00:39,670
we expect a multiplicative change in the odds of

13

00:00:39,670  -->  00:00:43,810
